    <etym xml:lang="ru">%iarv%i — закономерная перестановка из %i*avr%i и восходит к <mentioned
            xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>*abra-</w><gloss><q>облако</q></gloss></mentioned>; ср. <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_wad"/>; однако в других иранских (и индоевропейских) языках
        слово %iarv%i имеет соответствия со значением не ‘небо’, а ‘облако’, ‘туча’, ‘влага’:
            <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><lang/><w>awr, aur, haur</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="ps"><lang/><w>ōrə, owrai</w><gloss><q>облако</q></gloss></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"
            ><lang/><w>haur</w><gloss><q>дождь</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                ><lang/><w>abr, awr</w></mentioned> (последнее в диалектах), <mentioned
            xml:lang="pal"><lang/><w>awr(aβr)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"
                ><lang/><w>py-aura</w><gloss><q>облако</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="kho"><w>ora</w><gloss><q>Luftraum</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>awra-</w><gloss><q>облако</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><w/><gloss><q>дождь</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                ><lang/><w>abhrá-</w></mentioned> id., <mentioned xml:lang="grc"
                    ><lang/><w>ἀφρός</w><gloss><q>пена</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="xcl"><lang/><w>amp, amb</w><gloss><q>облако</q></gloss></mentioned>. Колебание
        значений ‘небо’ и‘облако’ находим и в других языках, ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
                ><lang/><w>небо</w></mentioned> при <mentioned xml:lang="sa-vaidika"
                ><lang/><w>nabhas-</w><gloss><q>облако</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="sa-vaidika"><w/><gloss><q>туман</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="grc"><lang/><w>νέφος</w><gloss><q>облако</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="grc"><w/><gloss><q>туман</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="en"
                ><lang/><w>sky</w><gloss><q>небоʼ, первоначально ‘облако</q></gloss></mentioned>. О
        перемещении значения ‘облако’ → ‘небо’ в связи с климатическими условиями см.:
                <bibl><author>W. Brandenstein</author><biblScope xml:lang="ru"> Bemerkungen zum
                Sinnbezirk des Klimas. Studien zur indogermanischen Grundsprache, 1952, стр.
                24—25</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en"> Bemerkungen zum Sinnbezirk des Klimas.
                Studien zur indogermanischen Grundsprache, 1952, pp. 24—25</biblScope></bibl>.
        Общеиранское слово для ‘неба’, <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>āsmān-</w></mentioned>,
        сохранилось, быть может, в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_az"/> | %ianz%i ‘год’ (см.). С
        %iarv%i связывают <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ævraǧ"/> ‘облако’ (см.).%n<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 50</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>14</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>23</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>18, 152, 199</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">%iarv%i is a natural methatesis of %i*avr%i and goes back to <mentioned
            xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>*abra-</w><gloss><q>cloud</q></gloss></mentioned>; cf. <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_wad"/>; however, in other Iranian (and Indo-European)
        languages, the word %iarv%i corresponds not to the meaning ‘sky’ but to ‘cloud’,
        ‘thundercloud’, ‘moisture’: <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><lang/><w>awr, aur,
            haur</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/><w>ōrə,
                    owrai</w><gloss><q>cloud</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/><w>haur</w><gloss><q>rain</q></gloss></mentioned>,
            <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>abr, awr</w></mentioned> (the latter attested in
        dialects), <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/><w>awr(aβr)</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>py-aura</w><gloss><q>cloud</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="kho"><w>ora</w><gloss><q>Luftraum</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>awra-</w><gloss><q>cloud</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="ae"><w/><gloss><q>rain</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                ><lang/><w>abhrá-</w></mentioned> id., <mentioned xml:lang="grc"
                    ><lang/><w>ἀφρός</w><gloss><q>foam</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="xcl"><lang/><w>amp, amb</w><gloss><q>облако</q></gloss></mentioned>. The
        fluctuation of the meanings ‘sky’ and ʽcloud’ is found in other languages, cf. <mentioned
            xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>небо</w><gloss><q>sky</q></gloss></mentioned> along with
            <mentioned xml:lang="sa-vaidika"
            ><lang/><w>nabhas-</w><gloss><q>cloud</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="sa-vaidika"><w/><gloss><q>fog</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="grc"><lang/><w>νέφος</w><gloss><q>cloud</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="grc"><w/><gloss><q>fog</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="en"
                ><lang/><w>sky</w><gloss><q>skyʼ, initially ‘cloud</q></gloss></mentioned>. On the
        semantic shift ʽcloud’ → ‘sky’ due to climatic conditions, see: <bibl><author>W.
                Brandenstein</author><biblScope xml:lang="ru"> Bemerkungen zum Sinnbezirk des
                Klimas. Studien zur indogermanischen Grundsprache, 1952, стр.
                24—25</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en"> Bemerkungen zum Sinnbezirk des Klimas.
                Studien zur indogermanischen Grundsprache, 1952, pp. 24—25</biblScope></bibl>. The
        common Iranian word for ʽskyʼ, <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>āsmān-</w></mentioned>,
        was probably preserved in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_az"/> | %ianz%i ‘year’ (see).
        %iarv%i is also being associated with <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ævraǧ"/> ‘cloud’
                (see).%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II
        50</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."
            /><biblScope>14</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."
                /><biblScope>23</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>18,
                152, 199</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
